00:09:49.040 --> 00:09:52.520
&gt;&gt; We begin with me
as a 4-year-old child

00:09:52.520 --> 00:09:54.190
who came from Pakistan.

00:09:54.190 --> 00:09:56.820
My father wanted a
better life for us.

00:09:56.820 --> 00:10:01.010
He wanted us to go to
school and I came to America

00:10:01.010 --> 00:10:05.040
and I remember being
called Hindu

00:10:05.040 --> 00:10:07.300
and being called all these names

00:10:07.300 --> 00:10:11.260
because kids just didn't
understand my culture

00:10:11.260 --> 00:10:13.740
and I would be like
embarrassed if my mother

00:10:13.740 --> 00:10:15.110
who wore the head scarf
would take me to school.

00:10:15.110 --> 00:10:18.260
As a child, you don't
know, because all you want

00:10:18.260 --> 00:10:22.020
to do is fit in and I
remember I was in fourth grade

00:10:22.020 --> 00:10:24.100
and I had a crush
on this Greek boy.

00:10:24.100 --> 00:10:25.930
His name was Leo something.

00:10:25.930 --> 00:10:28.150
It's a long last name.

00:10:28.150 --> 00:10:31.680
And, I remember thinking to
myself why even look at him,

00:10:31.680 --> 00:10:33.020
Nyla [assumed spelling]
when you know you're going

00:10:33.020 --> 00:10:34.580
to marry someone else.

00:10:34.580 --> 00:10:38.790
Imagine what that's like for
someone in the fourth grade.

00:10:38.790 --> 00:10:42.870
So, in October of 2004,
I went to Pakistan.

00:10:42.870 --> 00:10:44.870
They said oh it's
your cousin's wedding.

00:10:44.870 --> 00:10:49.350
You know that was the trick to
get me there, that we were going

00:10:49.350 --> 00:10:52.820
for my cousin's wedding and
the next thing you know,

00:10:52.820 --> 00:10:54.740
January 5th came along

00:10:54.740 --> 00:10:57.010
and that's the day my
whole life changed.

00:10:57.010 --> 00:10:58.310
[ Music ]

00:10:58.310 --> 00:11:07.380
&gt;&gt; I think as a Muslim
American, as an Arab American

00:11:07.380 --> 00:11:10.830
who has grown up in the
United States his whole life,

00:11:10.830 --> 00:11:12.980
I was born and raised
here from parents

00:11:12.980 --> 00:11:14.730
who immigrated from Syria.

00:11:14.730 --> 00:11:18.930
Now, I think one of the main
reasons why I wanted to come

00:11:18.930 --> 00:11:24.320
down here and speak about
my story is because I am one

00:11:24.320 --> 00:11:27.660
of the very few Arabs or
Muslim Americans who decided

00:11:27.660 --> 00:11:32.230
to branch off from being a
doctor or engineer or lawyer

00:11:32.230 --> 00:11:35.700
and do something
completely out of the norm.

00:11:35.700 --> 00:11:39.020
And so, right now I
am a videographer.

00:11:39.020 --> 00:11:41.410
I've been doing video,
telling stories

00:11:41.410 --> 00:11:43.890
for about nine to ten years now.

00:11:43.890 --> 00:11:47.200
I'm not in it for the money
and I'm not in it for the fame.

00:11:47.200 --> 00:11:49.500
I'm in it for the next
generation that is to come.

00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:53.090
The next generation out
there who are like my brother

00:11:53.090 --> 00:11:55.740
or my sister or even my kids,
I want them to grow up knowing

00:11:55.740 --> 00:11:57.580
that they can be
something that they want,

00:11:57.580 --> 00:11:58.880
that they can put their mind to.

00:11:58.880 --> 00:12:00.660
You can be a firefighter.

00:12:00.660 --> 00:12:03.740
You can be a - someone that
wants to be on the news,

00:12:03.740 --> 00:12:06.840
someone that wants to do
something in PR, communications.

00:12:06.840 --> 00:12:10.510
Anything that you can put your
mind to, you should go for it.

00:12:10.510 --> 00:12:15.160
