dream has been different?

00:59:37.540 --> 00:59:41.710
&gt;&gt; We have about a couple
of minutes to answer this

00:59:41.710 --> 00:59:46.030
and there's a couple
more questions, so.

00:59:47.050 --> 00:59:50.080
&gt;&gt; I'm not sure I understood
the question exactly,

00:59:50.080 --> 00:59:54.910
but with regard to hate
crimes and their affect

00:59:54.910 --> 00:59:57.910
on the Muslim American
community, I definitely feel

00:59:57.910 --> 01:00:01.820
that there's a greater sense of
trepidation among communities

01:00:01.820 --> 01:00:04.740
about what's going on and what
the appropriate response should

01:00:04.740 --> 01:00:09.650
be, especially considering we're
three examples of individuals

01:00:09.650 --> 01:00:14.400
and families that have tried to
I think in our own ways just to,

01:00:14.400 --> 01:00:16.160
you know, work and
mind our own business

01:00:16.160 --> 01:00:17.460
like everybody else
does, you know,

01:00:17.460 --> 01:00:19.040
in their respective
communities across the nation.

01:00:19.040 --> 01:00:22.300
I think it's - with respect

01:00:22.300 --> 01:00:27.780
to the individuals perpetrating
the crime, I think that's

01:00:27.780 --> 01:00:29.080
where your question was going.

01:00:29.080 --> 01:00:31.740
I think that's where
communication is needed

01:00:31.740 --> 01:00:35.210
and there is related
more to ignorance

01:00:35.210 --> 01:00:38.640
than necessarily racism even
need to be responded to.

01:00:38.640 --> 01:00:42.050
I - I think that, this is my
personal opinion, no MALA's,

01:00:42.050 --> 01:00:45.190
but a hyper-partisan political
environment doesn't help.

01:00:45.190 --> 01:00:47.320
We need to talk to
each other more.

01:00:47.320 --> 01:00:49.240
We need to have projects

01:00:49.240 --> 01:00:55.970
like MALA's narrative project be
expanded into more communities.

01:00:55.970 --> 01:00:58.890
And, you know, for the questions
regarding to demographics

01:00:58.890 --> 01:01:00.990
that haven't been
included yet, that -

01:01:00.990 --> 01:01:02.420
that's a factor of funding.

01:01:02.420 --> 01:01:04.400
[Inaudible] organization
which, you know,

01:01:04.400 --> 01:01:07.810
I don't fund myself
or get a salary from.

01:01:07.810 --> 01:01:10.420
They work really hard to try
to raise the money they can

01:01:10.420 --> 01:01:16.180
to get people taped and it's
not [inaudible] aren't easy.

01:01:16.180 --> 01:01:18.410
They're not making
anybody money.

01:01:18.410 --> 01:01:20.500
So, nonprofits like [inaudible]

01:01:20.500 --> 01:01:26.110
or any other community oriented
project needs public support.

01:01:26.110 --> 01:01:28.790
And, it'll reach the
demographics you're seeing -

01:01:28.790 --> 01:01:31.340
where you're seeing the gaps
if that support happens.

01:01:31.340 --> 01:01:35.510
And, the second part of
your question was about --

01:01:35.510 --> 01:01:39.330
[ Inaudible Response ]

01:01:39.330 --> 01:01:40.630
&gt;&gt; -- salvation.

01:01:40.630 --> 01:01:43.540
They do - they affiliate
