01:01:43.540 --> 01:01:47.270
from the American dream or
they have the same take --

01:01:47.270 --> 01:01:48.570
&gt;&gt; I - I think it varies.

01:01:48.570 --> 01:01:49.870
I think it varies.

01:01:49.870 --> 01:01:52.760
I mean, I think when an audience
member, you know, raised concern

01:01:52.760 --> 01:01:56.480
with that feeling of, you
know, victimization, I -

01:01:56.480 --> 01:01:58.970
I think it's how the
issues are spoken about.

01:01:58.970 --> 01:02:03.480
I personally feel more strongly
that every immigrant community

01:02:03.480 --> 01:02:06.330
that has come into the
United States regardless

01:02:06.330 --> 01:02:09.970
of era has faced its unique
challenges and Muslims are going

01:02:09.970 --> 01:02:14.060
to face their challenges given
the political backdrop we find

01:02:14.060 --> 01:02:15.360
ourselves in.

01:02:15.360 --> 01:02:16.670
A hundred years from now,

01:02:16.670 --> 01:02:18.230
I don't know what other
communities are going

01:02:18.230 --> 01:02:21.460
to face integration issues,
but it's a part of growing.

01:02:21.460 --> 01:02:24.630
Like, to me, what America
is, what America means,

01:02:24.630 --> 01:02:27.420
that identity, it's life
and organic and it changes

01:02:27.420 --> 01:02:31.190
and its influx and it's what you
contribute, what you take back

01:02:31.190 --> 01:02:35.360
and it goes back to
communication and respect.

01:02:35.360 --> 01:02:37.500
Even especially where
you see the differences.

01:02:37.500 --> 01:02:41.140
That's where the communication
needs to happen ten times more.

01:02:41.140 --> 01:02:43.580
And, we can't look at
each other caricatures,

01:02:43.580 --> 01:02:45.860
which I think is the
issue on all sides

01:02:45.860 --> 01:02:49.290
and that's my politics
and not Zainab's.

01:02:49.290 --> 01:02:51.000
&gt;&gt; I - I mean I think
