01:08:49.010 --> 01:08:51.190
Now, before we get
started with that,

01:08:51.190 --> 01:08:53.710
I'd like to talk a little bit
about StoryCorps for those

01:08:53.710 --> 01:08:55.580
of you who are unfamiliar
with us.

01:08:55.580 --> 01:08:57.960
So, StoryCorps is
an independent,

01:08:57.960 --> 01:09:02.010
nonprofit organization
that was founded in 2003

01:09:02.010 --> 01:09:05.050
by radio documentarian
Dave Isay.

01:09:05.050 --> 01:09:07.910
Now, our mission is
relatively simple.

01:09:07.910 --> 01:09:12.140
It is to record, preserve
and share humanity stories

01:09:12.140 --> 01:09:17.820
and in pursuit of this mission,
we hope to really build a sense

01:09:17.820 --> 01:09:24.140
of compassion and empathy
throughout humanity as well.

01:09:24.140 --> 01:09:25.760
So, this is how it works.

01:09:25.760 --> 01:09:27.430
We have recording locations

01:09:27.430 --> 01:09:30.230
in San Francisco,
Atlanta, and Chicago.

01:09:30.230 --> 01:09:32.070
We also have a mobile
booth that travels

01:09:32.070 --> 01:09:35.820
around different cities each
month recording stories.

01:09:35.820 --> 01:09:38.430
And, we have what's called
a national team in New York

01:09:38.430 --> 01:09:41.260
which is based out of New
York, but they travel all

01:09:41.260 --> 01:09:44.870
over the country
recording stories as well.

01:09:44.870 --> 01:09:48.550
And so, you might come into one
of our booths with a friend,

01:09:48.550 --> 01:09:51.360
a family member, someone
you know or someone you'd

01:09:51.360 --> 01:09:52.970
like to get to know
a little bit more

01:09:52.970 --> 01:09:56.610
and you have a 40-minute
conversation with that person.

01:09:56.610 --> 01:09:59.310
It would be recorded by one
of our trained facilitators

01:09:59.310 --> 01:10:03.500
who would be taking notes during
the process and afterwords,

01:10:03.500 --> 01:10:05.050
of course, you would receive
a copy of the interview.

01:10:05.050 --> 01:10:09.810
And, with the participants
permission, we would also add

01:10:09.810 --> 01:10:12.370
that interview to the
StoryCorps archive.

01:10:12.370 --> 01:10:14.260
Now, every interview
that is part

01:10:14.260 --> 01:10:17.640
of the StoryCorps archive is
actually housed right here

01:10:17.640 --> 01:10:20.830
at The Library of Congress, at
the American Folklife Center.

01:10:20.830 --> 01:10:24.230
So, those of you who are
interested in hearing some

01:10:24.230 --> 01:10:27.420
of these stories from the MALA
collection and other collections

01:10:27.420 --> 01:10:29.110
that we have in the
StoryCorps archive.

01:10:29.110 --> 01:10:31.400
You can make a reservation at
the American Folklife Center

01:10:31.400 --> 01:10:34.510
and go and listen to
some of the stories.

01:10:34.510 --> 01:10:39.420
We are hoping to put a large
portion of the archive online

01:10:39.420 --> 01:10:40.730
in the next year or so.

01:10:40.730 --> 01:10:44.340
So, stay tuned for
more details on that.

01:10:44.340 --> 01:10:46.760
So, at this point,
we've collected

01:10:46.760 --> 01:10:50.040
over 70 thousand interviews.

01:10:50.040 --> 01:10:55.040
Now, you cannot collect 70
thousand interviews in a silo.

01:10:55.040 --> 01:10:59.590
We rely on partnerships like
MALA to reach participants,

01:10:59.590 --> 01:11:02.670
to create the archive
that we have today.

01:11:02.670 --> 01:11:05.340
And, we would be unable
to pursue our mission

01:11:05.340 --> 01:11:08.490
without the partners that
we work with like MALA.

01:11:08.490 --> 01:11:11.310
There would be very little
recording, preserving or sharing

01:11:11.310 --> 01:11:13.110
if we didn't have
any interviews.

01:11:13.110 --> 01:11:17.520
So, we see the stories in
our archive as contributions

01:11:17.520 --> 01:11:21.270
from participants and
organizations as well.

01:11:21.270 --> 01:11:23.570
So, I do want to make sure

01:11:23.570 --> 01:11:26.130
that everyone knows how
grateful StoryCorps is

01:11:26.130 --> 01:11:28.290
to be working with MALA.

01:11:28.290 --> 01:11:31.030
And, very, very grateful to be -

01:11:31.030 --> 01:11:33.480
to have been connected
with - with MALA.

01:11:33.480 --> 01:11:36.520
This happened back in 2014.

