01:13:03.290 --> 01:13:05.910
that are there and the
individuals who are part

01:13:05.910 --> 01:13:09.810
of this archive, part of
this journey's collection.

01:13:09.810 --> 01:13:13.400
Now, some of the themes that
you'll hear are about home,

01:13:13.400 --> 01:13:19.520
acceptance, identity, culture,
music, art, resilience.

01:13:19.520 --> 01:13:21.060
Some of these are
traumatic stories.

01:13:21.060 --> 01:13:25.320
Some of these stories are about
painful events, but they're also

01:13:25.320 --> 01:13:28.270
about love and laughter
and hope.

01:13:28.270 --> 01:13:33.370
The people who are presenting
their stories are artists,

01:13:33.370 --> 01:13:38.450
visionaries, thinkers, writers,
creators, content producers,

01:13:38.450 --> 01:13:42.210
educators, activists,
friends and family members,

01:13:42.210 --> 01:13:45.030
colleagues, mentors and mentees.

01:13:45.030 --> 01:13:47.010
There are so many
different types of stories

01:13:47.010 --> 01:13:50.150
that are being told and so
many types of participants

01:13:50.150 --> 01:13:54.920
who are part of this project.

01:13:54.920 --> 01:13:58.990
In addition, there are dozens
of countries represented.

