01:21:58.330 --> 01:21:59.890
in a broad number
of them actually,

01:21:59.890 --> 01:22:04.790
it seemed like maybe Islam and
Muslim were not explicitly put

01:22:04.790 --> 01:22:07.040
in and yet, maybe there
are themes around it

01:22:07.040 --> 01:22:09.150
or maybe it was part -

01:22:09.150 --> 01:22:11.260
it was part of this
collection in some way.

01:22:11.260 --> 01:22:15.160
And, so I think it - it
comes back to - over here,

01:22:15.160 --> 01:22:16.780
here's another really good one

01:22:16.780 --> 01:22:19.990
where the different keywords
included for example advice,

01:22:19.990 --> 01:22:24.570
aging, art, college,
divorce, ethnic identity,

01:22:24.570 --> 01:22:26.920
cultural expectations,
independence,

01:22:26.920 --> 01:22:28.750
leadership, volunteerism.

01:22:28.750 --> 01:22:31.990
And, these were definitely
very broad applicable themes

01:22:31.990 --> 01:22:34.770
on this interview.

01:22:34.770 --> 01:22:38.210
But, maybe if I had
been looking for this

01:22:38.210 --> 01:22:40.240
and it hadn't been
labeled as part of MALA,

01:22:40.240 --> 01:22:41.780
I would not have
found this collection.

01:22:41.780 --> 01:22:45.450
So, if somebody came in and said
I want, you know, this interview

01:22:45.450 --> 01:22:49.620
about Muslims - this interview,
for example, would have not -

01:22:49.620 --> 01:22:51.800
would have not come
up in the search,

01:22:51.800 --> 01:22:54.560
but I also think maybe it wasn't
- maybe it wasn't relevant.

01:22:54.560 --> 01:22:57.530
Going back to some of the
excerpts that we heard earlier,

01:22:57.530 --> 01:23:01.070
maybe this person didn't feel
comfortable self-identity

01:23:01.070 --> 01:23:07.100
strictly as Muslim or maybe
this person was atheist, but,

01:23:07.100 --> 01:23:10.100
you know, had some sort

01:23:10.100 --> 01:23:12.950
of cultural relationship
or - of some kind.

01:23:12.950 --> 01:23:16.030
So, I think it's -
it's interesting to -

01:23:16.030 --> 01:23:20.020
to think about how these
labels are very important

01:23:20.020 --> 01:23:23.110
and they have a very, very
practical usage, so we have -

01:23:23.110 --> 01:23:25.660
we have people coming
in all the time asking

01:23:25.660 --> 01:23:26.960
about the StoryCorps interviews,

01:23:26.960 --> 01:23:28.960
but also that there's a
high level of interpretation

01:23:28.960 --> 01:23:32.040
when you go home and use
your phone and use the app

01:23:32.040 --> 01:23:35.040
and that you can
self-identify if you want to.

01:23:35.040 --> 01:23:38.650
You can explicitly say I'm going
to identify as Korean American

01:23:38.650 --> 01:23:43.160
or I choose not to because
I feel like there's a sort

01:23:43.160 --> 01:23:45.650
of flattening affect
with the keywords

01:23:45.650 --> 01:23:49.650
or I just don't feel
comfortable with that.

01:23:49.650 --> 01:23:52.810
So, that's sort of
my ten minutes.

01:23:52.810 --> 01:23:56.370
But, I know you must think, wow,
this is chaotic, how do manage

01:23:56.370 --> 01:23:59.170
and classify when you
have 80,000 interviews.

01:23:59.170 --> 01:24:01.560
I'm just going to point out that
there's - there's a whole system

01:24:01.560 --> 01:24:04.750
in place where we - at
the library and archivists

01:24:04.750 --> 01:24:06.540
and librarians here
do this professionally

01:24:06.540 --> 01:24:10.930
and their categories and ways to
do this, so this is a snapshot

01:24:10.930 --> 01:24:15.980
of our authority list,
specifically around Muslim.

01:24:15.980 --> 01:24:19.250
So, there're - there are
whole areas of study here,

01:24:19.250 --> 01:24:21.110
but the point of the
app and in some ways one

01:24:21.110 --> 01:24:22.410
of the great things
about the app is

01:24:22.410 --> 01:24:26.550
that it embraces your own
interpretation and that if -

01:24:26.550 --> 01:24:28.950
when - as you - when you -
when you go home and contribute

01:24:28.950 --> 01:24:32.120
to this, you can do
whatever you want in terms

01:24:32.120 --> 01:24:35.820
of identifying yourself or not.

01:24:35.820 --> 01:24:38.690
So, I would encourage you
to use the app and come

01:24:38.690 --> 01:24:43.690
and use your collections and
sort of keywords in ten minutes.

01:24:43.690 --> 01:24:45.490
Thank you.

